HEADWORD: Prochronism
<hw>Pro"chro*nism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
preceding in time; <?/ before + <?/ time: cf. F.
<ets>prochronisme</ets>.]</ety> <def>The dating of an event before the
time it happened; an antedating; -- opposed to
<ant>metachronism</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

